        "publisher": "HarperCollins Publishers", 
        "rating": "4.5", 
        "review": "In Garth Stein's novel, Fido speaks. Well not exactly speaks, but pooch Enzo does narrateThe Art of Racing in the Rain. From his floor-hugging position, this restless Lab-terrier mix dispenses trenchant views on life, car racing, and his nominal owner, Denny Swift. Stein's daring use of a four-legged narrator doesn't distract us from the story of would-be NASCAR driver Swift; in fact, it effectively lightens the tone of Denny's bumpy ride.", 
