        "publisher": "Doherty, Tom Associates, LLC", 
        "rating": "4.5", 
        "review": "According to a 1996New York Timesarticle, 'Robert Jordan has come to dominate the world that Tolkien began to reveal.' Robert Jordan is hands-down the most widely read and talked-about fantasy author writing today. His mammoth, multivolumeNew York Timesbestselling Wheel of Time series has sold more millions of copies to date. Book One of the Wheel of Time isThe Eye of the World,a staggeringly complex and enjoyable adventure that's not without its own cast of unforgettable characters: Rand, a simple sheepherder who is stalked by an evil he does not yet understand; Egwene, Rand's love interest, who happens to possess her own very special gift; Moraine, the beautiful but possibly dangerous member of a powerful legion of sorceresses called Aes Sedai; and Lan, Moraine's fearless companion and guardian.--Andrew LeCount", 
