        "rating": "3.5", 
        "review": "Bestseller Coben (Hold Tight) has a knack for taking everyday nightmares and playing with life&rsquo;s endless &ldquo;what ifs,&rdquo; as shown in this stand-alone thriller, a tightly choreographed dance of guilt and innocence, forgiveness and retribution. Frank Tremont, a world-weary, near-retirement investigator for New Jersey&rsquo;s Essex County, has to face his failure to solve his last case&mdash;the disappearance of a teenage girl. Meanwhile, Dan Mercer stands accused of being a sexual predator thanks to the ambush journalism of Wendy Tynes, a tabloid TV reporter, who must cope with her husband&rsquo;s death caused by a drunken driver as well as reckon with the possibility of Mercer&rsquo;s innocence. When Tynes finds a link between a father of one of Mercer&rsquo;s alleged victims and others felled by scandal, she could become a killer&rsquo;s next victim. If the wealth of characters dilutes the suspense, Coben gives readers lots to think about when judging rights and wrongs. 500,000 first printing; 12-city author tour. (Mar.)", 
