        "review": "When Rosie Daly didn't show up to go to London, Dubliner Frank Mackey concluded that his fianc&eacute; had silently dumped him. Twenty-two years later, after her suitcase turned up hidden behind a fireplace, he started to have second thoughts&#151;and the police began to have very serious first suspicions. An arresting new mystery by the author of In the Woods, which won the 2007 Edgar Award for Best First Novel. Persuasive first-person narration; compelling atmosphere; plausible plot; solid reviews. Now in paperback and NOOKbook editions.", 
