        "review": "Jane Lindskold came to the attention of fantasy fans by finishing two books,DonnerjackandLord Demon, begun by the legendaryRoger Zelaznybefore his tragic death in 1995 at the age of 58, from colon cancer. Lindskold went on to create novels in her own right, and this effort could be described as a historic fantasy with touches of romance, intrigue, and myth. The story centers on Firekeeper, a teenage orphan who has been living in the wilderness with a pack of giant, intelligent wolves. Her world is turned upside down when an expedition arrives looking for the long-lost Prince Barden and his group. The girl, who can 'climb like a squirrel, swim like a fish and outrun a trotting horse,' knows that she must confront the humans to find out more about her mysterious past. After meeting the group, it is speculated that this wild child could be the heir to the throne of Hawk Haven.", 
