        "pub_date": "May 2011", 
        "publisher": "Grand Central Publishing", 
        "rating": "4.5", 
        "review": "Before he became the star of his own late night namesake show, Jimmy Fallon starred on Saturday Night Live for five years. During that stint, he was well known for being unable to keep a straight face during skits. In these simulated thank you notes, however, he manages to keep his authorial tongue firmly planted in cheek while he expresses his 'gratitude' to Miley Cyrus, Hillary Clinton, and hundreds of others. Only you the reader will be laughing uproariously. A paperback original.", 
