        "isbn13": "9781603201278", 
        "listprice": "$29.95", 
        "price": "$18.26", 
        "pub_date": "October 2010", 
        "publisher": "Time Home Entertainment, Incorporated", 
        "rating": "0", 
        "review": "If you don't yet have a digital camera, you're probably the last person on your block with that dubious distinction. But don't despair&#58; Millions of these magical devices are hibernating in dark desk drawers, abandoned because new owners couldn't adequately master their labyrinthine instructions. The editors of LIFE and veteran photojournalist and photography book author Joe McNally set out to rectify that situation. Their guide to digital photography takes readers through every step; from learning terminology to selecting the right camera for you; to shot selection, focusing, lighting, and composition; to taking, saving, and transmitting pictures. LIFE Guide to Digital Photography features easy-to-understand step-by-step instructions and helpful pictures to enhance your camera skills. A one-stop snapshot college.", 
